    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-07-01T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-07-01T03:00:00-05:00" n="201"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d201">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/13351: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-07-01T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 1, 1938—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 1—7:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1038. Sun Fo<note n="84" xml:id="d201fn84">President of the Chinese Legislative
                        Yuan.</note> who returned to Paris recently from Moscow said to me that his
                    negotiations in Moscow had been most successful. The Soviet Government had
                    promised to continue to supply China with arms and munitions on credit. He
                    asserted that six Japanese divisions had lost all their heavy artillery and
                    tanks as a result of the Yellow River inundations. He added that he believed
                    that the Japanese offensive against Hankow would be held up for many months and
                    reaffirmed the determination of the Chinese Government to continue to fight to
                    the end.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
